                            <comment id="25355" author="mdiep" created="Tue, 3 Jan 2012 13:30:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Per BrianM comment about the Release&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;If we are going to start building iokit RPMs the implication is that they will get distributed eventually, either officially or unofficially.&lt;br/&gt;
To that end, I would suggest that the Release: value remain untouched by us. It&apos;s typically for downstream packagers anyway and should only be incremented when there are changes that only affect the build within a given version (that should be rare for us once this has all been implemented).&lt;br/&gt;
I would further suggest that a &quot;bugfix&quot; be added to the Version: and that given the iokit&apos;s relative stability that we be religious about incrementing the bugfix or the minor version component of the version for each landing depending on whether it&apos;s an enhancement of some sort or a bug fix.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
